messages.content: cuz I have to talk first because usually would say hi this is so and so thank you for joining the interview but I have a buck so I'll stop talking
No problem at all! Let's get started then. Can you share with me what first sparked your interest in fly fishing?
I was fly fishing with my grandfather pop in Colorado and he showed me how to make with little bit of string and a hook a fake fly and we actually caught fish on it I found that fascinating
That sounds like a wonderful experience with your grandfather! Can you tell me more about what fascinated you about the process of fly fishing and making your own fake fly?

I found interesting that in such small crates you could go play and splash in the water like a little kid and you throw this thing back and forth back and forth and then Wham official come from the bottom and eat it
That sounds like a fun and exciting experience! Can you tell me more about the feeling of playing and splashing in the water while fly fishing? What makes it enjoyable for you?
